From: Oren Ben-Kiki <oren&capella.co.il>
To: iana&iana.org, oren&capella.co.il
Subject: Request for MIME media type Application/Vendor Tree - vnd.

Name : Oren Ben-Kiki

E-mail : oren&capella.co.il

MIME media type name : Application

MIME subtype name : Vendor Tree - vnd.publishare-delta-tree

Required parameters : None.

Optional parameters : 
An optional version parameter in the format "V<int>.<int>" may be
specified.  The first integer is the major version number, the second
is the minor version number.  The version numbers indicate upward
compatibility; a version is upward compatible with another if it has
the same major version number and a greater or equal minor version
number.  The currently valid version number is "V1.0".


Encoding considerations : 
Documents of this type contain binary data and should be suitably
encoded for transfer.


Security considerations : 
This type may contain embedded JavaScript fragments which are run on
the client (via a browser).  All the capabilities available to embedded
JavaScript code are available to such code.  The code is subject to the
usual security checks placed on embedded JavaScript code.  In addition,
this type may contain application-specific data whose sensitivity
depends on the specific application.  Therefore in some cases
manipulation of objects of this type should be done via secured
mechanisms (for example, transfer via HTTPS).

Interoperability considerations : 
Interoperates only on platforms supported by the PubliShare run-time
environment.


Published specification : 
Not available. Objects of this type may be interpreted using the
PubliShare run-time environment available from Capella Computers Ltd.


Applications which use this media : 
Used only by the PubliShare run-time environment.


Additional information :

1. Magic number(s) : 
2. File extension(s) : qps
3. Macintosh file type code : 
This type is used to transfer data from the PubliShare server to the
PubliShare run-time environment.  PubliShare
(http://www.publishare.com) is a Web-enabled electronic publishing
system developed by Capella Computers Ltd.


Person to contact for further information :

1. Name : Oren Ben-Kiki
2. E-mail : publishare-delta-tree&capella.co.il

Intended usage : Limited Use 


Author/Change controller : Capella Computers Ltd.
